"cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM". 

The paper proposes a method for reducing the number of parameters in Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for distributed machine learning and AI-enabled edge devices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces an auxiliary neural network for generating convolutional filters, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The method involves training the parameters of the auxiliary network and their corresponding code vectors instead of the filters of the convolutional layers, which relates to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on ResNet and DenseNet models, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
